<span id="freeTextContainer3345547438043676004">I read this compendium of Poe&apos;s stories while still at high-school. <br/>Loved it then and love it now.<br/>Poe was a trailblazer in the mystery, suspense and horror genres and his writing has been hugely influential, changing the world of literature. <br/>&quot;The Murders in the Rue Morgue&quot;, considered the first modern detective story, is a short masterpiece. Grisly and gory by the standards of its day, this tale is well worth a read today, as are all the other wonderful tales in this collection of Poe&apos;s works. I</span>
  <span id="freeText3345547438043676004" style="display:none">I read this compendium of Poe's stories while still at high-school. <br />Loved it then and love it now.<br />Poe was a trailblazer in the mystery, suspense and horror genres and his writing has been hugely influential, changing the world of literature. <br />"The Murders in the Rue Morgue", considered the first modern detective story, is a short masterpiece. Grisly and gory by the standards of its day, this tale is well worth a read today, as are all the other wonderful tales in this collection of Poe's works. In particular, "The Tell-Tale Heart" and "The Pit and the Pendulum".</span>
