<span id="freeTextContainer13955003570637773535">A very nice edition, I bought this as a reading copy from Barnes and Noble this Christmas after I had stumbled across a gorgeous original 1920s edition with all of Harry Clarke&apos;s original artwork in it. I did not want to add wear to that large volume by actually reading it from cover to cover, so I was happily surprised to find this copy. Not all of Clarke&apos;s brooding, creepy, beautiful Art Nouveau artwork is included in this edition, but it does include most of it. I am not sure why some was not</span>
  <span id="freeText13955003570637773535" style="display:none">A very nice edition, I bought this as a reading copy from Barnes and Noble this Christmas after I had stumbled across a gorgeous original 1920s edition with all of Harry Clarke's original artwork in it. I did not want to add wear to that large volume by actually reading it from cover to cover, so I was happily surprised to find this copy. Not all of Clarke's brooding, creepy, beautiful Art Nouveau artwork is included in this edition, but it does include most of it. I am not sure why some was not included--some of the work is quite risquee--but not more so than several pieces included in this volume. I would recommend going on Amazon or Ebay and finding one of the original copies (they ARE there), but this version is great to actually read, especially if you do not already have a Complete Poems and Tales of E.A.P. in your library. </span>
