    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_896139016" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/896139016" />
    <a title="Jari Van den bossche" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27976789-jari-van-den-bossche"><img alt="Jari Van den bossche" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610665890p2/27976789.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/896139016?book_show_action=true">Mar 30, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jari Van den bossche" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jari Van den bossche" href="/user/show/27976789-jari-van-den-bossche">Jari Van den bossche</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer896139016" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4477496549535006544">Outside, the sky started to grow dark and purple, as a bruise. I closed the curtains and lit the candles. I opened the thick, old book covered by a thin layer of dust that had just lain in front of me... <br/>And then ...<br/><br/>Then, I got lost. For a couple of hours, I lost all my senses and disappeared from the place that humans call earth. For this period, while I was reading, I wasn&apos;t attainable ... <br/>It felt like I was in another place. A place, where the 19th century Master of horror had transported me.</span>
  <span id="freeText4477496549535006544" style="display:none">Outside, the sky started to grow dark and purple, as a bruise. I closed the curtains and lit the candles. I opened the thick, old book covered by a thin layer of dust that had just lain in front of me... <br />And then ...<br /><br />Then, I got lost. For a couple of hours, I lost all my senses and disappeared from the place that humans call earth. For this period, while I was reading, I wasn't attainable ... <br />It felt like I was in another place. A place, where the 19th century Master of horror had transported me. A dim, dusky space. Almost like a vacuum. The only air left to inhale was just enough to absord his dark and killing words ...<br />The tension rose and I got terrified! Doors started slamming, floors were creaking, wind was howling, candles were blown out ... And then, I awoke ... I found myself in complete darkness. After having peered in the darkness for about ten minutes, I could distinguish the outlines of the furniture in the living room. I was back into reality ...<br /><br />I was completely blown away by the book. It's true what I was told. Poe is indeed the master of writing the most eerie stories. <br />According to me, his descriptions just make his tales so eerie and so alive. I warmly recommend the M. Valdemar tale and also 'The Black Cat'. I finished reading them with goosebumps and I got shives all over my body ... <br /><br />So why did I give this nightmare delivering book only 3 stars? <br />Well, because of the terribly annoying stories about detective Dupin. I beg you: don't start reading the murders in the rue Morgue or the Mystery of Marie Roget! I had to force myself to finish them ... just terrible! These stories shall be read by me NEVERMORE!<br /><br />So, that explains the 3 starts ...But actually, the book deserves 3.5 starts because of the love stories ...<br />I'd never expected them to be that good. How could an almost psychiatric, death-loving men write love stories that are so sincere and passionate? It's possible ... They were definitely not my favorites 'cause they can't exceed his horror tales, but I did appreciate them. <br /><br />It's a must read if you're keen on horror or the old English language use. Or well, both of them. <br /><br />This book shall be remembered EVERMORE!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4477496549535006544" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

